label: abbreviation textual entity
definition: A textual entity listing abbreviations and their expansions that are used in a document.

label: achieves_planned_objective
definition: This relation obtains between a planned process and a objective specification when the criteria specified in the objective specification are met at the end of the planned process.

label: agent-level ecosystem census
definition: A data set that is the specified output of a agent-level ecosystem data generation that had census data as an input.

label: aggregate of disease courses
definition: A process that (1) has as occurrent parts at least two disease courses that realize the same type of disease, and (2) has as participants two or more hosts that are members of a particular host population.
term_editors: William R. Hogan; Amanda Hicks; Matthew Diller

label: alternative term
definition: An alternative name for a class or property which means the same thing as the preferred name (semantically equivalent)

label: atmospheric data set
definition: A data set that is about either the Earth's atmosphere or some part of the Earth's atmosphere.

label: bearer of
definition: a relation between an independent continuant (the bearer) and a specifically dependent continuant (the dependent), in which the dependent specifically depends on the bearer for its existence

label: case series data set
definition: A data set that is the output of a case series investigation.

label: center
definition: An organization where a specified activity is concentrated.; A place where a particular activity or service is concentrated.

label: climate data set
definition: A data set that is an aggregate of data items that are about an environmental system process (e.g., hydrological precipitation) or a participant in an environmental system process.

label: college
definition: A primary academic unit within a University or a free-standing higher education organization without graduate degree programs.; A primary academic unit within a University or a free-standing higher education organization without graduate degree programs

label: compiled software code
definition: A software that is the specified output of some compilation of software process
editor_preferred_term: machine instructions compiled from software source code

label: compiling software
definition: A planned process that converts human-written or curated software into a machine-executable or interpretable set of instructions.

label: computer cluster
definition: A group of linked computers, working together closely so that in many respects they form a single computer.

label: count of cases in an epidemic
definition: A count of disease cases in an infected population that meet the case definition criteria within a particular epidemic interval.

label: count of disease cases
definition: A count of individuals in a population who meet the criteria of some case definition during some time interval.

label: creating a copyright license
definition: A planned process that has a copyright license as its specified output.

label: data encoding
definition: a documenting process to encode an information entity into a digital document

label: data format specification
definition: A data format specification is the information content borne by the document published defining the specification.

label: data format validator
definition: A software that takes a data set as input and outputs a determination of whether the dataset is in compliance with one or more given data format specifications.

label: data parsing
definition: A data transformation that has a dataset, encoded in a particular data format specification, as input and extracts certain elements or parts of the dataset, typically into the volatile memory of a computer.

label: data service software
definition: A software that implements a data service.

label: data set
definition: A data item that is an aggregate of other data items of the same type that have something in common. Averages and distributions can be determined for data sets.

label: data visualizer software
definition: A planned process that has some data visualizer software objective specification as part.

label: dataset creating
definition: A planned process that has a data set as its specified output.

label: denotes
definition: denotes is a primitive, instance-level, relation obtaining between an information content entity and some portion of reality. Denotation is what happens when someone creates an information content entity E in order to specifically refer to something. The only relation between E and the thing is that E can be used to 'pick out' the thing. This relation connects those two together. Freedictionary.com sense 3: To signify directly; refer to specifically

label: department
definition: A unit within a larger organization that addresses a specific subject or area of activity.

label: diagram
definition: A figure that expresses one or more propositions

label: digital curation
definition: Digital curation is the process of establishing and developing long term repositories of digital assets for current and future reference by researchers, scientists, and historians, and scholars generally.

label: digital object identifier
definition: A centrally registered identifier symbol used to uniquely identify objects given by International DOI Foundation. The DOI system is particularly used for electronic documents such as journal articles.

label: disease surveillance data
definition: A data set that is about some disease surveillance.

label: disease transmission model
definition: An algorithm that models the progress of a transmissible disease in a population.

label: disease transmission tree estimator
definition: An algorithm that has specified output some transmission tree.

label: division
definition: A major unit or section within a larger organization.

label: DNA sequence data
definition: A sequence data item that is about the primary structure of DNA

label: document
definition: A collection of information content entities intended to be understood together as a whole

label: editor preferred term
definition: The concise, meaningful, and human-friendly name for a class or property preferred by the ontology developers. (US-English)

label: epidemic data set
definition: A data set about an instance of an epidemic.

label: epidemic peak intensity
definition: A predicted data item that is about some aggregate of cases in an epidemic and whose value specification contains the maximum value in a data set that is about the epidemic.
term_editors: Matthew Diller; Amanda Hicks; William R. Hogan

label: epidemic peak week
definition: A scalar value specification whose measurement unit label is 'week', and that is part of the epidemic peak intensity.
term_editors: William R. Hogan; Matthew Diller; Amanda Hicks

label: epidemic start week
definition: A scalar value specification whose measurement unit label is 'week' and that is part of the first predicted data item that is greater than the epidemic threshold set for that data item.
term_editors: Matthew Diller; William R. Hogan; Amanda Hicks

label: Example: The ISO document specifying what encompasses an XML document; The instructions in a XSD file"
female gender role
definition: A gender role borne by a human being that is realized in behaviour which is considered socially appropriate for individuals of the female sex in the context of the culture in question.

label: gender role
definition: A human social role borne by a human being being realized in behaviour which is considered socially appropriate for individuals of a specific sex in the context of a specific culture.

label: genomic data
definition: Genomic data is data about the genomes of an organism.

label: government agency
definition: A unit of government responsible for oversight and regulation of certain activities or the administration and provision of specific services.

label: has basis in
definition: (Q is_a Quality ⋀ D is_a Disposition ⋀ Q base of D) ® ∀q (q instance_of Q ® b (q inheres_in b ⋀ d (d instance_of D ⋀ d inheres_in b)))

label: has proper continuant part at some time
has value specification
definition: A relation between an information content entity and a value specification that specifies its value.

label: has_specified_input
definition: A relation between a planned process and a continuant participating in that process that is not created during  the process. The presence of the continuant during the process is explicitly specified in the plan specification which the process realizes the concretization of.
term_editors: PERSON: Larry Hunter; PERSON: Melanie Coutot; PERSON: Bjoern Peters; PERSON: Alan Ruttenberg

label: has_specified_output
definition: A relation between a planned process and a continuant participating in that process. The presence of the continuant at the end of the process is explicitly specified in the objective specification which the process realizes the concretization of.
term_editors: PERSON: Alan Ruttenberg; PERSON: Larry Hunter; PERSON: Bjoern Peters; PERSON: Melanie Courtot

label: hospital
definition: An institution that provides medical, surgical, psychiatric or nursing care.

label: host population
definition: A population of organisms some of which were susceptible to infection with a particular pathogen at some point in their lives.

label: human readable synopsis
definition: A comment that summarizes the most relevant or salient features and history of the entity for human readers.

label: infectious disease forecast objective specification
definition: An objective specification that is realized by the estimation of one or more predicted data items that are about 1) some infection in ecosystem and 2) potential changes to its number of participants (e.g., individuals within a host population, individuals within a vector population) relative to a particular temporal region; and is part of some infectious disease forecasting software.

label: infectious disease forecasting software
definition: Simulation software that has as output one or more predicted count data items that are about a host population and that predict how many infections will occur at or will have occurred at some temporal region relative to when the data items are created.

label: infectious disease nowcast objective specification
definition: An infectious disease forecasting objective specification that is realized by the estimation of one or more predicted data items that are about some infection in ecosystem as they are occurring in real time, and is part of some infectious disease nowcasting software.

label: infectious disease scenario
definition: A dataset that represents at least one pathogen population (of a particular biological taxon) in one host population (of a particular biological taxon) in an ecosystem in a particular location at a particular point in time.

label: information carrier
definition: A quality of an information bearer that imparts the information content

label: institute
definition: An Institute normally has a research focus but may also fulfill instructional or outreach roles; An organization founded to pursue or promote certain research, educational or public policy interests or activities.

label: is about
definition: is_about is a (currently) primitive relation that relates an information artifact to an entity.

label: is concretized as
definition: A relationship between a generically dependent continuant and a specifically dependent continuant, in which the generically dependent continuant depends on some independent continuant in virtue of the fact that the specifically dependent continuant also depends on that same independent continuant. A generically dependent continuant may be concretized as multiple specifically dependent continuants.

label: is contact information about
definition: a is contact information for b, if a is a information content entity, b is a human being or an organization and a identifies a physical location or electronic resource that allows to initiate communication with a.

label: is realized by
definition: Relation between a realizable and a process. Reciprocal relation of realizes [GOC:cjm]
alternative_terms: executed_during; realized_by; has_realization; realized by; is_realized_as

label: Laboratory
definition: An organizational unit (as opposed to the physical facility) that performs research, provides services, or processes materials

label: legal person role
definition: A role borne by a human individual or by a collection of humans regarded as possessing rights and duties enforeable at law.

label: located in
definition: a relation between two independent continuants, the target and the location, in which the target is entirely within the location

label: male gender role
definition: A gender role borne by a human being that is realized in behaviour which is considered socially appropriate for individuals of the male sex in the context of the culture in question.

label: material entity
definition: An independent continuant that is spatially extended whose identity is independent of that of other entities and can be maintained through time.

label: member of
definition: is member of is a mereological relation between a item and a collection.
alternative_terms: is member of; member part of

label: mortality data
definition: A data set that is about either some mortality rate or the death events themselves of some individuals of a given population of a particular biological taxon.

label: obsolete has active participant
definition: x has participant y if and only if x realizes some active role that inheres in y

label: ORCID
definition: An identifier curated by ORCID, Inc. to denote some academic author.

label: organization
definition: An organization is a continuant entity which can play roles,  has members, and has a set of organization rules.  Members of organizations are either organizations themselves or individual people. Members can bear specific organization member roles that are determined in the organization rules. The organization rules also determine how decisions are made on behalf of the organization by the organization members.
term_editors: PERSON: Bjoern Peters; PERSON: Susanna Sansone; PERSON: Philippe Rocca-Serra; PERSON: Alan Ruttenberg

label: part of
definition: a core relation that holds between a part and its whole

label: pathogen evolution model
definition: Simulation software that simulates the evolution over time of a particular pathogen of a particular biological taxon.

label: plan specification
definition: a directive information entity that when concretized it is realized in a process in which the bearer tries to achieve the objectives, in part by taking the actions specified. Plan specifications includes parts such as objective specification, action specifications and conditional specifications.

label: planned process
definition: A processual entity that realizes a plan which is the concretization of a plan specification.

label: population
definition: A collection of organisms, all of the same species, that live in the same place.

label: population census
definition: The outcome of a population survey.

label: population demographic census
definition: A data set that is the specific outcome of a population demographic survey.

label: population dynamics model
definition: An algorithm that simulates changes in the size and life stage distribution of a population or populations of organisms of a particular biological taxon.

label: postal address
definition: A textual entity that is used as directive to deliver something to a person, or organization

label: program
definition: An ongoing academic initiative not formalized with department or division status.

label: programming language
definition: A language in which source code is written that is intended to be executed/run by a software interpreter. Programming languages are ways to write instructions that specify what to do, and sometimes, how to do it.

label: proper name
definition: A proper name is an information content entity that is the outcome of a dubbing process and is used to refer to one instance of entity shared by a group of people to refer to that individual entity.

label: proper part of continuant at all times
definition: b proper_continuant_part_of c at t =Def. b continuant_part_of c at t  & b and c are not identical. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [004-001])

label: publication
definition: A document that has been accepted by a publisher

label: scalar value specification
definition: A value specification that consists of two parts: a numeral and a unit label

label: school
definition: An institution for instruction in a particular skill or field.

label: simulates
definition: a simulates b, iff a is a purely intentional entity that is representing a fictional individual or fact b and a participates in a simulating.

label: simulating of process of type X
definition: a planned process that (1) has at least one process part that has as participants representations of participants (in place of those participants) of processes of type X, and where all such process parts substitute for parts of processes of type X, and (2) is carried out for the purpose of planning for processes of type X, learning more about processes of type X, or teaching about processes of type X.

label: simulation of population
definition: A simulation of a population or populations of organisms of a particular biological taxon that simulates a particular type of event or types of event that occur in a specified time interval.

label: simulation time step action specification
definition: An action specification that specifies the length of the time steps interval assumed in a simulation.

label: software development
definition: A planned process resulting in a software product involving the creation of source code.

label: software execution
definition: A planned process that realizes the concretization of a software.

label: software license
definition: A copyright license that is about some software and contains one or more conditional specifications that specify the use and redistribution of the software.

label: software license version identifier
definition: An identifier that, as part of a complete software license identifier, refers to one specific version of the software license.

label: software version identifier
definition: An identifier that, as part of a complete software identifier, refers to one specific version of the software.

label: source code repository
definition: A data set that comprises at least one set of source code files for software as well as provenance information about who contributed the set of files, and optionally multiple versions of files with detailed change history about who committed files and when, a license for the software, readme files, documentation, executables, etc.
editor_preferred_term: software source code version control repository

label: specifically depends on at some time
study design
definition: A plan specification comprised of protocols (which may specify how and what kinds of data will be gathered) that are executed as part of an investigation and is realized during a study design execution.

label: study design execution
definition: a planned process that carries out a study design

label: synthetic ecosystem constructor
definition: A software that when compiled and run, has specified output of an agent-level ecosystem data set.
alternative_terms: software for creating a synthetic ecosystem dataset

label: telephone number
definition: A telephone number is a sequence of digits assigned to a fixed-line telephone subscriber station connected to a telephone line or to a wireless electronic telephony device, such as a radio telephone or a mobile telephone, or to other devices for data transmission via the public switched telephone network (PSTN) or other public and private networks.

label: time measurement datum
definition: A scalar measurement datum that is the result of measuring a temporal interval

label: time sampled measurement data set
definition: A data set that is an aggregate of data recording some measurement at a number of time points. The time series data set is an ordered list of pairs of time measurement data and the corresponding measurement data acquired at that time.

label: treatment facility census
definition: A census that counts the number of treatment facilities of some kind in a particular geographical region.
alternative_terms: treatment facilities census; census of treatment facilities; treatment facility census

label: university
definition: An institution of higher education and research, which grants academic degrees in a variety of subjects, and provides both undergraduate education and postgraduate education.

label: version number
definition: A version number is an information content entity which is a sequence of characters borne by part of each of a class of manufactured products or its packaging and indicates its order within a set of other products having the same name.

label: web service execution
definition: A software execution that is provided by the web service, and involves invoking software execution over network.

label: website
definition: A set of related web pages containing content such as text, images, video, audio, etc., prepared and maintained as a collection of information on a particular subject.

label: website with data
editor_preferred_term: website that has data as a part

label: weighted arithmetic mean
definition: The weighted arithmetic mean is a measure of central tendency that is the sum of the products of each observed value and their respective non-negative weights, divided by the sum of the weights, such that the contribution of each observed value to the mean may defer according to its respective weight. It is defined by the formula: A = sum(vi*wi)/sum(wi), where 'i' ranges from 1 to n, 'vi' is the value of each observation, and 'wi' is the value of the respective weight for each observed value.; The weighted arithmetic mean is a kind of mean similar to an ordinary arithmetic mean (the most common type of average), The weighted arithmetic mean is often used if one wants to combine average values from samples of the same population with different sample sizes." except that instead of each of the data points contributing equally to the final average, some data points are weighted, meaning they contribute more than others.
term_editors: Matthew Diller; Alejandra Gonzalez-Beltran; Philippe Rocca-Serra; Orlaith Burke
